 The G37, political support group, has applauded president-elect, Bola Ahmed Tinubu, on his victory at the 2023 presidential poll, saying his emergence would ensure continuity of good governance by the President Muhammadu Buhari-led administration. National coordinator of the group, Comrade Evans City, who stated this in Abuja in a statement issued yesterday said Nigerians did a good job by voting Tinubu as the next president of the country. City equally commended  national chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Sen Abdullahi Adamu, as well as members of G37 group across the country for contributing immensely to the victory of the party at all levels. He stated: “I will specifically thank the former board member of Niger Delta Development Commission, NNDC. Honourable, Evang Caroline Barine Nagbo for her support and effort towards the victory of Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu in Rivers State and South-South and her motherly support to G-37 Group.” He charged aggrieved members of the opposition to drop their swords and embrace peace for the progress of the country adding that the people have spoken.